column5: I'm tying some of that up right now actually

ice fish rainbows!

Just noticed, did you actually go out and drill a hole? LOL Something tells me he didn't drill a hole.  Might have been a boot...
No and to be honest I did not even walk on it. I only agreed with Wayne cause it seemed funny. Went back today and the ice is gone and a couple of boats were launched.  Oh well
No time for perch this year. Walleye, pike, trout. Soooo much trout. Oh and burbot.

No time for perch this year. Walleye, pike, trout. Soooo much trout. Oh and burbot. So Simcoe? BTW, did your number change when you moved?
Wasn't responding to Wayne but to this, sure looks like something went through...   yeah, rock to check thickness

Went around the bay on the way home.Saw 3 guys in a bass boat just east of hooters in Barrie.Real troopers,it was a bit cold for sure.Wonder if there OFC members?Only boat out there,would nice to hear a report.One thing I was impressed with the orange floater suits(I think there floaters).Looked warm and ready for any bad thing that may happen.Heaven forbid.
I know why they are out there. End of season. I would of loved to be out there today.
We are talking Simcoe here.....I would not be overly surprised if somebody tried to park their truck on it.
We are talking Simcoe here.....I would not be overly surprised if somebody tried to park their truck on it. The DARWIN awards will come soon enough.
We are talking Simcoe here.....I would not be overly surprised if somebody tried to park their truck on it. ya, but I can take my snowmobile out on it right?
Get Terry to go out and jump up and down on it first just to make sure!!!
Cooks Bay I wonder how many will try walking on it this weekend     ok might take a little bit more cold to make it safe
Your socks dry yet????
Your socks dry yet????
just one sock and work boot drying nicely thanks....lol
Some people are easy to read.... LMAO !!
You' have to be nuts to go out there this weekend. Hopefully no one is dumb enough to go out there.... It might be their last....
You' have to be nuts to go out there this weekend. Hopefully no one is dumb enough to go out there.... It might be their last....  Live a little.LMAO
Freezing up quite nicely in Ottawa and area, the next couple nights will see -24 to -26 temps. Looks like we might be fishing before xmas.
Woohoo, might get an early start this year

We're always fishing before Christmas Matt.. but I was hoping for it to be in a boat before Muskie closes on the 15th!! Looking like I might have to go sharpen up the auger and get ready for my usual trip with Lloyd and Terry to a little lake we know that we're usually ice fishing before Christmas.  Seems to be a few lakes around with 4" on them already... but the snow today and yesterday sure won't help make it safe.
I think it was about 4-5 years ago my bud and I were fishing walleye January 7th from a boat. Strange, kinda neat but would rather have been on the ice.
Your socks dry yet????   Too perfectly witty!  Bring on a day of icing pannies to thicken the blood... then let the real blood bath begin.
You mean to tell me that there's lakes with no ice yet?
Well, the girlfriend isn't going to be happy, but looks like I'm going to be able to do a lot of ice fishing over the Christmas break.
Lets hope this cold weather continues. Early season!

We are super lucky here... There are spots that'll be frozen enough you could ice fish this weekend... Yet I'll be out in the boat.... We have no break between ice up and boat season... Spring or fall...  Most years I'm able toget out past New Years...

Well most of sturgeon lake in the kawarthas froze over now !!!! I knew as soon as the wind died down it would freeze and it's -15 here now in bobcaygeon with no wind so it should be real tight soon !!!!! Awesome ......
Same for Clear Lake east of you Shawn, it was wide open Wednesday and frozen right across last night.  Kinda pretty right now too with the crescent moon shining on the ice.
-22 in Angus this morning, that should give old man Simcoe the chills..

Well, the girlfriend isn't going to be happy, but looks like I'm going to be able to do a lot of ice fishing over the Christmas break. Trooper! -20 this morning, clear skies and low winds. Nipissing will have a good skim as well.
Temps aren't looking good for icemaking next week.  Let's hope the winds stay down.
Well, the girlfriend isn't going to be happy, but looks like I'm going to be able to do a lot of ice fishing over the Christmas break. Going to go for another try at "perch power up"?
Temps aren't looking good for icemaking next week.  Let's hope the winds stay down.  Party Pooper!!
Lots of steel to catch, not worried about ice just yet
